reviewText: A delightful little movie about a hapless small-town journalist on the edge of unemployment. Then he meets a small-town girl who just happens to be a cat. Together they take on "the man" and discover love.Sure, totally impossible, but in a movie era saturated with giant robots, flying superheros, gods, spooks, monsters, aliens and magic, this is considerably more believable--and fun!
Title: N/A

reviewText: I don't know a lot about dutch cinema, haven't even seen a lot of dutch movies, but a lot of the dutch films I have seen (specially comedies) seem to me to be consistently great, generally commercial but very entertaining and thought provoking. This is apparently based on a very popular children's book I haven't read. A cat turns into a woman after coming across some chemical stuff spilled from a barrel. She finds herself transformed into a woman on the rooftops of her small town. Eventually, she takes refuge in the apartment of a struggling but honest reporter, and through her ability to communicate with her fellow cats, she helps him expose a case of local corruption (a scoop that saves him from being fired from his newspaper). This movie wouldn't work as well as it does without the charming perfomance of Carice Van Houten (she starred in Paul Verhoeven's Black Book) as the titular woman/cat. Theo Massen's performance as the shy reporter is also great.
summary: Dutch film for children is wholly enjoyable

reviewText: What's weird is that the spooky and unaccountable MPAA had slapped an "R" rating ("brief language, smoking, and rude behavior") on this movie when the DVD was mastered. Not cited are the far worse depictions of cats being kicked, hit with a bottle, and shot at, and of a child being struck by the main Bad Guy. Strangely however, the current rating online and on the DVD carton is "PG".For those parents who actually care to guide their children, and engage in a little perspective-building dialog after a family viewing, this is a fine, harmless movie. The Bad Guy gets his comeuppance, community standards of moral behavior are demonstrated, and the protagonists reach a satisfactory conclusion. Miss Minoes is free of the usual creepy and politically-correct subtexts that permeate most American-made kids' films these days.BTW the original Dutch dialog track is to be recommended.
summary: Mostly-harmless fun for kids of all ages

reviewText: I had never heard of the children's book or movie until I saw a reference to the movie online.  Being a cat lover, I couldn't resist watching a movie about a cat who turns into a human.  I think it's a great film for all ages.  Ms. Van Houten is superb as Miss Minoes, and though the voices are dubbed into English, it's done so well, you hardly notice.  A very few instances of profanity are in the film, but given the deterioration of our society, children today cannot help but be exposed to profanity everywhere they go.  I believe that responsible parents teach their children not to use such words, and the so-called profanity in this film is very mild in comparison to what one can hear on the street during the course of a normal day.

reviewText: Miss Minoes, which was released theatrically just a few months ago, is a wonderful film to serve as an introduction to foreign cinema for children. The upcoming DVD will release with two audio tracks: One is the original Dutch with English subtitles and the second is a well done English dubbing. This permits children to choose how they might want to listen to it. The theatrical was in English and my 11 yr old and I thoroughly enjoyed it.The story is of a feline who turns into a young woman and befriends a journalist who is in desperate need of news to keep his job. The feline/woman enlists the help of the local cats who begin to serve as a news gathering service.The premise of Miss Minoes is adorable. The cats are adorable and the story line is well paced for 7-12 year olds. If you happen to be a fan of Russian Blues, even better, as there is a host of kittens.
summary: Great Introduction to International Film for children

reviewText: This movie is well directed and well acted.  The content will entertain children and adults alike.  Even if you like dogs, but don't like cats, you can't help but like this movie.About the only complaint I have is that the movie was dubbed into English.  I prefer to hear the original dialogue because there is an inevitable oversight of implied intent given by an inflection of the actor's voice that sometimes can't be voiced in English.  I find this can sometimes change the meaning of the storyline enough to make the movie disappointing for me.My dislike of dubbing aside, if you want to enjoy a lighthearted movie that can be shared with the entire family, this movie is a great one to watch.
summary: A movie even dog lovers will like

reviewText: Miss Minoes a wonderful story of a female Cat becoming a Human.  This movie gives you plenty of laughs and joy to see the bad Rich Business Man get taken down for his phoney, so called Reputation in a town with Human Animal Lovers.  The Reporter is helped by our Friend Miss Minoes, who is now Human and is the secretary of our Reporter, who is trying both to find Courage for themselves.  Miss Minoes is Very Afraid of Dogs, as most Cats are, unless they are brought up with Dogs.  Our Reporter gets over his Fear of Writing a Good Article for the Newspaper he is Employed by.  This is a wonderful Foreign Movie with Great Actors that will win your hearts for the great things they do together in saving their town and Cat Friends, as well as Humans Friends from the Rich Business Man who is using toxic chemicals in deodorant to make himself Rich, while not carrying a bit what he is doing to others he sells his poison deodorant to people in the town and the rest of their Country.  See if Miss Minoes played by Carice van Houten stays a Human or becomes a Cat again.The great part it has a Happy Ending and find out what happens to Miss Minoes and her Boss the Reporter it is and was a joy to watch a movie for the young and young of heart.Follow the Link below for a great Friday or Saturday night with your children:B008B8U3N2
summary: Miss Minoes a Movie for the Verty Young and Young at Heart a joy to see how Cats worked so well with these actors
